      'pdf-to-png':{
        page_title:'PDF to PNG Converter Free | Convert PDF Pages to PNG — RelahConvert',
        h2a:'How to Convert PDF to PNG Without Uploading',
        steps:['<strong>Select your PDF file</strong> — click "Select PDF" or drag and drop a PDF document onto the page. The tool reads the file straight from your device.','<strong>Pick an output DPI</strong> — 150 DPI is great for screen use, 300 DPI for print. Higher numbers mean sharper images and larger files.','<strong>Click Convert to PNG</strong> — every page of the PDF is rendered as a separate PNG image inside your browser. No upload, no waiting on a server.','<strong>Download your PNG images</strong> — save individual pages or grab everything in one ZIP file when your PDF has multiple pages.'],
        h2b:'The Best Free PDF to PNG Converter That Never Uploads Your Files',
        body:'<p>Need to extract pages from a PDF as PNG images? RelahConvert turns every page of a PDF into a high-quality PNG you can use in slideshows, reports, blog posts, or social media. The whole conversion runs locally inside your browser using PDF.js — your document never leaves your device, and there is no file size cap imposed by a remote server.</p><p>Set the output DPI to balance image sharpness against file size. 150 DPI produces crisp screen-ready PNGs. 300 DPI matches print quality. Multi-page PDFs are bundled into a single ZIP download for convenience, and each page is also available as an individual PNG download. There is no watermark, no account required, and nothing is uploaded.</p>',
        h3why:'Why Convert PDF to PNG?',
        why:'PNG is the best format when you need to share, embed, or edit specific pages of a PDF as standalone images. Unlike JPG, PNG is lossless and supports transparency, so text and diagrams stay sharp. Converting PDF pages to PNG lets you paste them into Word, Google Docs, Notion, Figma, Canva, or any image-only platform without dealing with PDF readers.',
        faqs:[
          {q:'How do I convert a PDF to PNG without uploading it anywhere?',a:'Use RelahConvert. Select your PDF file and the tool renders every page to PNG entirely inside your browser using PDF.js. Nothing is uploaded to any server, so even confidential documents stay private.'},
          {q:'Can I convert every page of a multi-page PDF to PNG at once?',a:'Yes. The PDF to PNG tool processes all pages of your document in a single click. Each page becomes its own PNG image, and you can download them individually or as a single ZIP archive.'},
          {q:'What DPI should I choose when converting PDF to PNG?',a:'150 DPI is the sweet spot for screen use, blog posts, and slide decks. Use 300 DPI if you plan to print the PNGs or zoom in heavily. For thumbnails or quick previews, 96 DPI keeps file sizes very small.'},
          {q:'Will the PNG images keep the same quality as the original PDF?',a:'Yes — PDF pages are vector content, so the converter rasterises them at whatever resolution you choose. Higher DPI means sharper text and graphics. PNG is a lossless format, so no extra compression damages the result.'},
          {q:'Is there a file size or page count limit?',a:'There is no hard limit imposed by RelahConvert because everything runs locally. The practical limit is your device memory — most modern phones and laptops handle 100+ page PDFs without trouble.'},
          {q:'Does the converter work with password-protected PDFs?',a:'PDFs without a password work instantly. For password-protected PDFs, please remove the password first using your PDF reader, then upload the unlocked file to the converter.'},
          {q:'Do you store my PDF or the converted images?',a:'Never. The whole conversion happens locally in your browser. We do not have access to your files at any point — they are not uploaded, logged, or stored.'},
        ],
        links:[{href:'/png-to-jpg',label:'PNG to JPG'},{href:'/jpg-to-pdf',label:'JPG to PDF'},{href:'/png-to-pdf',label:'PNG to PDF'},{href:'/compress',label:'Compress Image'}],
      },
